HEADWORD: Crissal
<hw>Cris"sal</hw> <pr>(kr?s"s<it>a</it>l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Pertaining to the crissum; <as>as,
<ex>crissal</ex> feathers</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having highly colored under tail coverts; <as>as,
the <ex>crissal</ex> thrasher</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crisscross</ent>⟦br⟧
